👗 AI Outfit Designer for Tailors

Project Description

AI Outfit Designer for Tailors is a modern web application that allows tailors and customers to design custom outfits digitally using artificial intelligence. The app helps users visualize clothing ideas, generate outfit suggestions, and manage design preferences easily.

Purpose of the Project

This project was built to help tailors and fashion designers simplify the outfit design process by using AI to generate creative clothing ideas. It solves the problem of manual sketching and difficulty in explaining design ideas between customers and tailors.

Tech Stack

React – Used to build the user interface and create a fast, responsive frontend.

Supabase – Handles authentication, database storage, and backend services.

Hugging Face – Provides AI models to generate outfit descriptions and design suggestions.


Key Features

User registration and login system

AI-generated outfit design suggestions

Save and manage custom outfit designs

Responsive modern user interface

Dashboard for managing user designs

Secure authentication using Supabase


Installation / Setup Steps

1. Clone the repository:

git clone https://github.com/your-username/your-IYF Capstone Project.git


2. Navigate into the project folder:

cd your-repository-name


3. Install dependencies:

npm install


4. Create a .env file in the root directory and add the required environment variables.


5. Start the development server:

npm run dev



Required Environment Variables

Create a .env file and add:

VITE_SUPABASE_URL=your_supabase_url
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_supabase_anon_key
VITE_HUGGINGFACE_API_KEY=your_huggingface_api_key

How to Run the Project

After installation, run:

npm run dev

Then open the local server link shown in the terminal (usually http://localhost:5173).

